21 Replace The SDDM Use sudo apt install sddm-theme-lubuntu Locate Available SDDM Themes If you’re getting “Permission denied” when trying to change SDDM to use the LXQt theme, it usually means you don’t have the right privileges or the file isn’t writable by your user. Here’s how to fix it:
Run sudo nano /etc/sddm.conf If the file doesn’t exist, create it with root Generate a default config: sudo sddm --example-config > /etc/sddm.conf then edit it sudo nano /etc/sddm.conf Set LXQt theme in the config
Inside /etc/sddm.conf, add: [Theme]
Current=lubuntu
Restart SDDM Using sudo systemctl restart sddm
Themes are usually stored in: /usr/share/sddm/themes/
